('4075', 'Process and Instrumentation Diagram', 'PandID - A diagram that shows all the relevant process and control information for each system using symbols and lines to represent equipment, piping, instrumentation, control devices, control philosophy/strategy and significant services. It is considered to be the master document to be used during Construction and Operation.', 'Tier 1', 'RLMU', 'P02', 'Flow Assurance', 'ASB, AFC, AFU, AFD', true, 1055),
('4078', 'Process Flow Diagram', 'PFD - A diagram used to define the process for a facility. There are many process/piping parameters listed on the PFD such as process flows, compositions, pressures and temperatures for each significant process and utility stream and for each operating case. Also called: Heat and Material Balance (H and MB, HMB), Process Scheme (PS).', 'Tier 1', 'RLMU', 'P02', 'Flow Assurance', 'ASB, AFC, AFU, AFD', true, 1056),
